  <brief_title>The Efficacy and Safety of Erdosteine in Chronic Obstructive Pulmonary Disease (COPD)</brief_title>
  <acronym>RESTORE</acronym>
  <official_title>The Efficacy and Safety of Erdosteine in the Long-term Therapy of Chronic Obstructive Pulmonary Disease (COPD). A 12-month, Randomised, Double-blind, Placebo-controlled, Parallel Group, Multicenter Study</official_title>
  <sponsors>
    <lead_sponsor>
      <agency>Edmond Pharma</agency>
      <agency_class>Industry</agency_class>
    </lead_sponsor>
  </sponsors>
  <source>Edmond Pharma</source>
  <oversight_info>
    <has_dmc>Yes</has_dmc>
  </oversight_info>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The aim of the study is to evaluate the effect of erdosteine, compared to placebo, on
      exacerbation rate over a 12-month treatment period in patients with moderate-to-severe COPD.
      Moreover, the effects of erdosteine on pulmonary function parameters, clinical symptoms and
      quality of life, and the long-term safety of the drug will be assessed.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
